## Problem

`createWorktree()` runs `npm install` in every new worktree, adding 10-30 seconds to dispatch latency even with a warm npm cache. All worktrees share the same `package.json` and `package-lock.json`, so the dependencies are always identical to the main repo.

## Design

In `src/lib/git.ts` (or wherever `createWorktree()` runs npm install), replace the `npm install` call with a symlink:

```typescript
// Instead of: execSync('npm install', { cwd: worktreePath })
// Do:
const mainNodeModules = join(repoRoot, 'node_modules');
const worktreeNodeModules = join(worktreePath, 'node_modules');
if (!existsSync(worktreeNodeModules)) {
  symlinkSync(mainNodeModules, worktreeNodeModules);
}
```

### Fallback
If `package-lock.json` in the worktree branch differs from the main repo's (i.e. the branch added/changed a dependency), fall back to running `npm install` for that worktree.

```typescript
const mainLock = readFileSync(join(repoRoot, 'package-lock.json'), 'utf8');
const worktreeLock = readFileSync(join(worktreePath, 'package-lock.json'), 'utf8');
if (mainLock !== worktreeLock) {
  execSync('npm install', { cwd: worktreePath });
} else {
  symlinkSync(mainNodeModules, worktreeNodeModules);
}
```

### Cleanup
When the worktree is removed, the symlink is automatically removed with it — no special cleanup needed.

## Files
- `src/lib/git.ts` — find the `npm install` call in `createWorktree()` and replace with symlink logic

## Acceptance criteria
- New worktrees are created without running `npm install` when package-lock.json matches
- Dispatch latency drops by 10-30 seconds
- Falls back to `npm install` when package-lock.json differs
- Existing worktree cleanup logic still works correctly

checkOrphanedWorktrees() at doctor.ts:237 calls extractPid(activeRun.session_key) to detect live processes. For SDK pipeline runs, session_key format is 'foreman:sdk:<model>:<uuid>' — no PID. extractPid() returns null, isProcessAlive(null) returns false, so the worktree is flagged as a zombie even when the agent is actively running.

The dedicated zombie run check (checkZombieRuns, line 389) correctly handles this via isSDKBasedRun(), returning 'pass' for SDK runs. But checkOrphanedWorktrees has its own inline zombie detection that lacks this guard.

Affected seeds during this session: bd-9dlq, bd-u5oq, bd-vjaj, bd-zwtr — all actively running (confirmed via foreman status) but flagged as zombies by the worktree check.

Fix: in checkOrphanedWorktrees around line 237, add the same isSDKBasedRun() guard:
  if (activeRun.status === 'running') {
    if (isSDKBasedRun(activeRun.session_key)) {
      // SDK runs — no PID to check, assume alive
      results.push({ status: 'pass', ... });
    } else {
      const pid = extractPid(...);
      // existing PID-based check
    }
  }

