## Fix in src/orchestrator/doctor.ts — orphaned worktree deletion

In the 'no runs' branch (currently line ~301 in checkOrphanedWorktrees), before calling removeWorktree(), add a git remote branch check:

### New helper function

```typescript
async function branchExistsOnOrigin(projectPath: string, seedId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  try {
    const result = execFileSync('git', [
      '-C', projectPath,
      'ls-remote', '--exit-code', 'origin',
      `refs/heads/foreman/${seedId}`
    ], { stdio: 'pipe', timeout: 10000 });
    return result.length > 0;
  } catch {
    return false; // ls-remote failed or ref not found
  }
}
```

### In the no-runs branch

Replace the current removeWorktree() call in the orphan case with:

  const onOrigin = await branchExistsOnOrigin(projectPath, seedId);
  if (onOrigin) {
    results.push({
      name: `worktree: ${seedId}`,
      status: 'warn',
      message: `Orphaned worktree has branch on origin — skipping deletion. Manually run: foreman merge --seed ${seedId} or git push origin --delete foreman/${seedId}`,
    });
  } else {
    // Safe to delete — no local run AND no remote branch
    await removeWorktree(projectPath, worktreePath);
    results.push({ name: `worktree: ${seedId}`, status: 'fixed', message: 'Removed orphaned worktree (no run, no remote branch)' });
  }

### Tests

- orphaned worktree + branch on origin: doctor warns, does NOT remove
- orphaned worktree + no branch on origin: doctor removes
- mergedRun worktree: doctor removes (existing behaviour unchanged)

## Fix in src/orchestrator/agent-worker.ts finalize()

Read the push result at lines 578-589. pushSucceeded is already tracked as a local variable.

### Change 1: Guard closeSeed behind pushSucceeded

Replace unconditional closeSeed at line 623:

  // BEFORE
  await closeSeed(seedId, config.projectPath);

  // AFTER
  if (pushSucceeded) {
    await closeSeed(seedId, config.projectPath);
    log('Closed bead %s (push succeeded, queued for merge)', seedId);
  } else {
    // Push failed — leave bead in_progress so it retries
    log('Skipping bead close for %s — push failed, bead stays in_progress', seedId);
    // Note: do NOT call resetSeedToOpen here — the bead should remain in_progress
    // so markStuck or next pipeline run can handle it. resetSeedToOpen is called
    // by markStuck in the failure path above.
  }

### Verify markStuck is called when push fails

Confirm that the push-failed branch (pushSucceeded=false) leads to markStuck() being called, which calls resetSeedToOpen(). If it does not, add the resetSeedToOpen call there too.

